A drug taken for non-[[medical]] reasons, usually for an exhilirating feeling or mind-altering effects.  In most cases, street drugs are illegal.  This term comes from the fact that these types of substances are normally sold '''on the street''' by drug dealers.

Examples of street drugs include [[Marijuana]], [[Cocaine]], [[Heroin]], [[Ecstasy]], [[LSD]], [[PCP]] and [[Methanphetamine]].